-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ed40550 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ed40550\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-64dbb3c\" data-id=\"64dbb3c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-86bdc81 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"86bdc81\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Squirrels Appearance<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c36ba84 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c36ba84\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The appearance of squirrels can vary depending on the species. The most common squirrel in Canada is the eastern gray squirrel, which has a distinctive gray fur, white underparts, and a bushy tail. They have small ears and sharp claws that help them climb trees and run swiftly along branches.<\/p><p>Another type of squirrel is the fox squirrel, which has reddish-brown fur with a distinct white belly. Their tails are also bushy but less large or fluffy than those of the eastern gray squirrel. On the other hand, ground squirrels have shorter tails and legs since they do not need to climb trees, but they have larger heads and bodies than tree-dwelling squirrels.<\/p><p>Squirrels also have large front teeth that never stop growing throughout their lives. These teeth are used to gnaw on nuts, seeds, fruits, and even bark. Additionally, their eyes are situated high on their head to provide better vision while climbing trees or running across open areas. Overall, squirrels&#8217; appearance allows them to adapt well to their environment while maintaining their unique charm.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-379ddee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"379ddee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitats<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0b307df elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"0b307df\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Squirrels are known for being one of the most common small mammals found in almost every part of the world. These creatures have adapted to living in various habitats, including forests, parks, gardens, and urban areas. Their ability to adapt to multiple environments is due to their flexible diet and behavioural patterns.<\/p><p>In the wild, squirrels live in hollow trees or nests made from twigs and leaves. These nests provide shelter and protection from predators. In urban areas, squirrels may choose to nest in attics or other structures that provide safety.<\/p><p>Squirrels are also excellent climbers and spend much of their time scurrying up trees or along power lines. They are well suited for this as they have sharp claws that allow them to grip onto surfaces tightly. Overall, squirrels&#8217; habitat is varied and adaptable, making them a common sight in many settings.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0390cc7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0390cc7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Squirrels\u200b Behaviour<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-01b1181 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"01b1181\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Squirrels are fascinating animals that exhibit a multitude of exciting behaviours. One of the most noticeable behaviours is their ability to climb trees easily. Squirrels have sharp claws that allow them to grip onto tree bark and climb up vertically, often in pursuit of food or safety. They can also jump from one tree branch to another, showcasing their incredible agility.<\/p><p>Another interesting behaviour is squirrels&#8217; tendency to store food for future use. This behaviour is known as caching, and it involves burying nuts and seeds in various locations throughout their habitat. Squirrels have an impeccable memory which allows them to remember where they&#8217;ve hidden their food even months after burying it.<\/p><p>Finally, squirrels exhibit social behaviour through their interactions with other species members. They communicate using vocalizations such as chirps and barks and engage in playful activities like chasing each other around trees or grooming one another&#8217;s fur.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-df8875b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"df8875b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Nutrition<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-049ea1b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"049ea1b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Squirrels are known for their love of nuts, particularly acorns and walnuts. They also eat seeds, fruits, and vegetables. Interestingly, squirrels have a unique digestive system that allows them to break down complex carbohydrates found in these foods. In addition to their typical diet, squirrels have been known to indulge in meat occasionally. They have been observed eating insects, bird eggs, and smaller rodents. This behaviour is more common among urban squirrels, who may have limited access to their traditional food sources.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5b0cba5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"5b0cba5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Potential Health Risks<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7f3781f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7f3781f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Squirrels may seem like cute and harmless creatures, but they can pose potential health risks to humans. One of the most significant risks is their droppings, which can transmit diseases such as salmonella and leptospirosis. These bacteria can easily transfer to humans through contact with contaminated surfaces or inhalation of dust particles containing the bacteria.<\/p><p>Another health risk associated with squirrels is their tendency to carry fleas and ticks that could spread various diseases. Lyme disease is a notable example, which can cause symptoms such as fever, fatigue, and joint pain in infected individuals. Moreover, squirrels are known carriers of hantavirus that can be transmitted through direct contact or inhalation of virus-contaminated urine or feces.<\/p><p>In conclusion, while squirrels may appear harmless on the surface, taking precautions is essential to avoid potential health risks. Always wear gloves when cleaning up squirrel droppings and avoid any direct contact with these rodents if possible. Additionally, keep your pets&#8217; flea and tick prevention treatments up-to-date if you live in an area where squirrels are prevalent. By taking these steps, you can significantly reduce your chances of contracting any illnesses from these little critters.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-b782683 elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b782683\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-deea05c\" data-id=\"deea05c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-329af4b\" data-id=\"329af4b\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0063b5d elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0063b5d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Humane Wildlife Removal Service<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a26c752 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a26c752\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Acme Pest Solutions offers humane wildlife removal services to ensure the safety and well-being of both animals and humans.<\/p><div class=\"flex-1 overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-vlfjz-79elbk h-full dark:bg-gray-800\"><div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-vlfjz-1n7m0yu\"><div class=\"flex flex-col items-center text-sm dark:bg-gray-800\"><div class=\"group w-full text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 border-b border-black\/10 dark:border-gray-900\/50 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-[#444654]\"><div class=\"text-base gap-4 md:gap-6 md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-xl xl:max-w-3xl p-4 md:py-6 flex lg:px-0 m-auto\"><div class=\"relative flex w-[calc(100%-50px)] flex-col gap-1 md:gap-3 lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\"><div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3\"><div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-4 whitespace-pre-wrap\"><div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\"><p>Our team at Acme Pest Solutions is trained to handle a variety of wildlife species and uses <strong>eco-friendly and humane<\/strong> methods to ensure the safety of both the animals and the environment.<\/p><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0193754 elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-4670 elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"0193754\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-lg\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/appointment\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Book An Appointment<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-d10e90e\" data-id=\"d10e90e\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-16904cf elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"16904cf\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-6f683d0\" data-id=\"6f683d0\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-63e9c83 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"63e9c83\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Prevention Methods<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f9555be elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f9555be\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Prevention methods are crucial to keeping squirrels from invading your home or garden. One way to deter squirrels is by placing mesh wire around the garden bed or using squirrel-proof bird feeders. Additionally, pruning tree limbs that are close to your roof can prevent squirrels from accessing it and potentially causing damage. It&#8217;s also important to seal any holes or cracks in the exterior of your home, such as in the attic, walls, or chimney.<\/p>\n<p>Along with squirrel prevention, if you have a home or barn or any other place where you are plagued by&nbsp;<u><b><a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/mice\/\">Mice<\/a><\/b><\/u>, we can help.<\/p>\n<p>Sometimes, homeowners may need to use repellents as a preventative measure against squirrels. These can include natural deterrents like predator urine or spicy substances like cayenne pepper. However, it&#8217;s important to note that these methods may not be effective for all situations and could potentially harm other wildlife in the area.<\/p>\n<p>Being proactive and taking preventative measures is key when dealing with squirrel infestations. By implementing these strategies, you can help ensure that your home and garden remain free of unwanted furry visitors.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-80f5be4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"80f5be4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Control &amp; Removal Strategies<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e57810f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e57810f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Squirrels are cute and fuzzy creatures that can be found in many parts of the Canada. While they may seem harmless, they can actually cause significant damage to gardens, homes, and other structures. If you have a squirrel problem on your property, it is important to implement control and removal strategies.<\/p><ul><li>One effective method for controlling squirrels is to remove their access to food sources. This means cleaning up any fallen fruit or nuts from trees and removing bird feeders that may attract them.<\/li><li>You can also install barriers around vulnerable areas of your home or garden, such as fencing around vegetable patches or mesh over attic vents.<\/li><li>In some cases, it may be necessary to trap and relocate squirrels from your property. However, this should only be done by trained professionals who can ensure the safety of both the animals and humans involved.<\/li><li>Additionally, it is important to check with local laws and regulations regarding trapping and relocating wildlife before taking any action.<\/li><\/ul><p>Controlling squirrel populations requires a combination of prevention tactics and humane removal methods to manage these adorable but potentially destructive critters effectively.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Squirrels Identification Color Size Description Color Squirrels have a uniform coat color that ranges from brownish-gray to black or reddish-brown. Size Squirrels can grow up to 27 inches in length. Description Squirrels have a unique body structure that enables them to move swiftly and effortlessly through trees. Their limbs are adapted for climbing with sharp &#8230; <a title=\"Squirrels\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/squirrels\/\" aria-label=\"More on Squirrels\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6644,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[37,36],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6450","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-pest-libraries","category-squirrels-control"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6450"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6450"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6450\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/6644"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=6450"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=6450"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=6450"}],"curies":[{"name":"